WHO   — ARTIFICIAL LIFE — a life-science sphere — the brainless mind
WHAT  — Life as a process, not a substance — and a process can run on anything. In a computer, simple rules conjure things that flock, hunt, heal their wounds, reproduce, and evolve, with no chemistry at all. Artificial life asks whether 'alive' is about what a thing is made of, or only about what it does.
WHERE — intelligence without a brain  Framework inputs: the living; the rule; the signal; the open question  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
